<TITLE> 3 killed in fire at N'ganj slum </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, Dec 24 (bdnews24.com)  Three people of a family, including a 4-year-old, died in a fire that broke out at a slum in Narayanganj town early on Thursday, police said. Narayanganj police chief Akhter Hossain said the fire at Rallibagan shanty of the town's Tanbazar area broke out at around 3am and gutted some around 40 dwellings. The dead have been identified as 25-year old Moni Rani, her 4-year old son Kishore Chandra and 65-year old mother Mono Rani. The three dead were family members of one Krishna, a garment factory owner, local people said. Firefighters doused the blaze after two hours of efforts. Police suspected the fire might have originated from electric short circuit or a mosquito coil. bdnew
